356
00:34:12,516 --> 00:34:14,603
Well, it's not you.

357
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:17,730
He just never got over it.

358
00:34:19,358 --> 00:34:23,487
He really loved your dad.
You should know that.

359
00:34:23,570 --> 00:34:25,865
- Did you?
- Of course.

360
00:34:28,367 --> 00:34:30,786
You do have a plan, though, right?

361
00:34:30,869 --> 00:34:33,539
I mean, we don't have to stay here forever?

362
00:34:33,581 --> 00:34:35,791
Sure, I do.

363
00:34:35,833 --> 00:34:39,670
Soon as I earn enough money,
I'm gonna get us right out of here.

364
00:34:39,753 --> 00:34:42,965
You know what?
What do you think about...

365
00:34:43,007 --> 00:34:44,925
Butt, Montana?

366
00:34:49,555 --> 00:34:53,058
Come on, let's play.
You don't know how to read anymore?

367
00:34:55,936 --> 00:34:57,563
Where'd the bottle come from?

368
00:34:58,814 --> 00:35:00,691
The granary.

369
00:35:00,775 --> 00:35:04,194
It's been there for a while.
Sometimes I just like to look at it.

370
00:35:04,278 --> 00:35:06,197
15, two.

371
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:08,574
You gonna open it?

372
00:35:08,616 --> 00:35:10,868
I'm not sure yet. 25.

373
00:35:10,951 --> 00:35:13,496
31 for two. Go.

374
00:35:14,705 --> 00:35:17,124
- Did you check on the bear?
- Eight.

375
00:35:17,166 --> 00:35:19,835
Yeah, you asked me to, didn't you?

376
00:35:20,585 --> 00:35:22,462
Here's a pair for two.

377
00:35:23,297 --> 00:35:25,382
I want you to feed him.

378
00:35:26,384 --> 00:35:28,428
- What?
- I want you to feed the bear.

379
00:35:28,512 --> 00:35:31,890
I don't trust Angie to feed
anything much past herself.

380
00:35:31,973 --> 00:35:35,852
"Feed the bear." "Please feed the bear."
"Bear, do you like bear shoes?"

381
00:35:35,936 --> 00:35:40,440
"What kind of food do you like, Bear?
Steak, chicken?"

382
00:35:40,523 --> 00:35:42,442
- Einar.
- What?

383
00:35:43,401 --> 00:35:45,528
Is her being here gonna ruin you?

384
00:35:47,864 --> 00:35:51,034
- The woman killed my son.
- Oh, come on.

385
00:35:51,117 --> 00:35:55,329
It was a car accident. They call them
accidents because it's nobody's fault.

386
00:35:55,413 --> 00:35:59,626
No, they call them accidents
to make the guilty feel better.

387
00:35:59,709 --> 00:36:03,004
- Is that so?
- I don't give a damn what they call them.

388
00:36:03,046 --> 00:36:04,965
My son's dead.

389
00:36:06,132 --> 00:36:08,051
Your granddaughter's not.

390
00:36:08,134 --> 00:36:10,052
And neither were you.

391
00:36:11,012 --> 00:36:15,308
Have you thought about
how she's gonna remember you?

392
00:36:16,143 --> 00:36:21,565
You know, come to think of it,
I don't feel like playing cards tonight.

393
00:36:21,606 --> 00:36:25,193
Put that bottle someplace
where I don't have to look at it.

394
00:37:21,625 --> 00:37:24,795
You know anything about pickup trucks?

395
00:37:26,839 --> 00:37:28,340
Aw, shit.

396
00:37:28,424 --> 00:37:32,844
Hand me that half-inch
socket wrench, would you?

397
00:37:32,886 --> 00:37:35,389
No, no, no.
Shiny one on the top.

398
00:37:36,181 --> 00:37:37,766
Yep.

399
00:37:38,934 --> 00:37:41,437
Do you wanna see what I'm doing?

400
00:37:45,607 --> 00:37:47,526
That's it.

401
00:37:49,278 --> 00:37:51,447
- OK, see these screws here?
- Mm-hm.

402
00:37:51,490 --> 00:37:56,244
This one I'm tightening, this holds
this thing up which holds the pan up.

403
00:37:56,327 --> 00:37:59,998
If this thing comes loose when you're
driving, you'll be sitting on the road.

404
00:38:00,081 --> 00:38:02,834
And that's not what you want to be doing...

405
00:38:02,876 --> 00:38:04,961
How come you and Einar don't get along?

406
00:38:05,045 --> 00:38:07,463
You're practically his daughter.

407
00:38:07,547 --> 00:38:10,008
What I am is his dead son's wife.

408
00:38:11,676 --> 00:38:16,056
He's always been really good to me.
He's the first friend I met here.

409
00:38:17,807 --> 00:38:20,560
I am not in the mood for their crap.

410
00:38:21,603 --> 00:38:22,771
I'll take 'em.

411
00:38:24,648 --> 00:38:28,693
- The special today is the enchilada plate.
- Thank you.

412
00:38:28,777 --> 00:38:32,572
They're good enchiladas.
Served by good people.

413
00:38:33,447 --> 00:38:35,366
I'm a good person.

414
00:38:36,326 --> 00:38:40,997
I'm also a woman who's taken more
than her fair share of shit off men.

415
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:43,041
Don't push me.

416
00:38:43,124 --> 00:38:47,212
I mean, I couldn't even take a pinch of crap
from two little cheesedicks like you.

417
00:38:47,295 --> 00:38:50,965
OK, crank it.

418
00:38:51,007 --> 00:38:52,926
Again.

419
00:38:53,926 --> 00:38:55,261
Again.

420
00:39:04,063 --> 00:39:06,190
Take your foot off the gas.

421
00:39:07,191 --> 00:39:09,318
Take your foot off the gas!

