at these good-looking sandwiches.

481
00:45:00,882 --> 00:45:03,384
There you go.
Hold it right about here.

482
00:45:03,467 --> 00:45:04,594
OK.

483
00:45:04,677 --> 00:45:09,391
- His foot's not gonna go anywhere.
- Oh, yes, it is. Look at that calf run.

484
00:45:09,432 --> 00:45:11,267
He's off and gone.

485
00:45:13,061 --> 00:45:16,105
Oops. That's a little bit low.

486
00:45:19,984 --> 00:45:22,570
- Yeah!
- I got it!

487
00:45:23,989 --> 00:45:26,432
- Look at that!
- Oh, yeah.

488
00:45:26,532 --> 00:45:30,036
Go on, try it again.
There you go.

489
00:45:34,623 --> 00:45:38,085
You got any more improvements
you wanna make around here?

490
00:45:38,169 --> 00:45:40,212
I thought I'd
straighten some of this mess.

491
00:45:40,254 --> 00:45:42,507
Thought Mitch might
want to work on something.

492
00:45:42,590 --> 00:45:46,344
- Did you ask him about it?
- Well, of course she did.

493
00:45:47,303 --> 00:45:50,264
Now that we've got interesting
company around here, I...

494
00:45:50,348 --> 00:45:52,391
I feel inspired.

495
00:45:54,935 --> 00:45:57,355
Excuse me.
I gotta go to work.

496
00:46:10,286 --> 00:46:12,246
You wanna know
what I dreamed last night?

497
00:46:12,329 --> 00:46:14,273
What?

498
00:46:14,373 --> 00:46:18,502
I dreamed you weren't
such a miserable son of a bitch.

499
00:46:19,295 --> 00:46:23,173
That's not dreaming.
That's wishful thinking.

500
00:46:24,049 --> 00:46:27,886
Did you hear anything
unusual last night?

501
